<p><strong>That=E2=80=99s why, we can use a third party package and that is=
 your NumPy .&nbsp;</strong>Using NumPy package, we can create single dimen=
sional as well as multi-dimensional arrays. By default NumPy package is not=
 available in python, you have to install it manually. We will see installi=
ng NumPy package later.</p>
<h3>NumPy Data Types</h3>
<h4>Numerical Types :</h4>
<ul>
<li>integers (int)</li>
<li>unsigned integers (uint)</li>
<li>floating point (float)</li>
<li>complex</li>
</ul>
<h4>Other Data Types</h4>
<ul>
<li>booleans (bool)</li>
<li>string</li>
<li>datetime</li>
<li>python object</li>
</ul>
